Part 1: Hello PHP
Create a PHP file called hello.php.

Write code to display:

Hello, World!
Modify your program so it displays your full name instead.

Part 2: Variables and Strings
Create a file called info.php.

Declare two variables: one for your name and one for your age.

Display a sentence such as:

My name is Alice and I am 20 years old.
Change the values and run the program again.

Part 3: Simple Calculator
Create a file called calculator.php.

Define two variables $num1 and $num2 with any numbers.

Write code to calculate and display the sum, difference, product, and quotient of the two numbers.
Example output:

The sum of 10 and 5 is 15 The difference of 10 and 5 is 5 ...
Part 4: Conditional Statements
Create a file called grades.php.

Define a variable $grade and assign it a number (0–100).

Write an if-elseif-else statement to display a letter grade:

90–100 → A

80–89 → B

70–79 → C

below 70 → Fail

Part 5: Loops
Create a file called loop.php.

Use a for loop to print numbers from 1 to 10.

Modify your code to print the multiplication table of 5 (e.g., 5 x 1 = 5).

Part 6: Form Handling
Create a file called form.php.

Build a simple HTML form with:

A text box for the user’s name.

A text box for the user’s age.

A submit button.

When the form is submitted, your PHP code should display a greeting such as:

Hello, Alice! You are 20 years old.
Challenge Task (Bonus)
Create a file called quiz.php that:

Asks the user to enter a number using a form.

Displays whether the number is even or odd using PHP.

Submission Requirements
Submit all .php files in a folder named CMPS361/Mod1/ in GitHub

Ensure your code runs without errors in XAMPP or another PHP server.

Include comments in your code explaining what each section does.

Create a video and post it here (DO NOT UPLOAD VIDEO, POST URL)
